### Complexity Analysis

* **Time Complexity: `O(2^(m + n))`**
  * Each `*` generates two recursive branches, one skipping characters, another consuming them.
  * This branching causes exponential growth, resulting in `O(2^(m+n))`.

* **Space Complexity: `O(m + n)`**
  * The recursion depth depends on the sum of string and pattern length.
  * Therefore, space usage comes mainly from the recursion stack at most linear in their lengths.


## Solution 2: Memoization (Top-Down Dynamic Programming)

### Intuition
* The recursive approach repeatedly solves the same subproblems, especially when encountering multiple `*` characters.  
* Memoization helps store results for each `(i, j)` pair — meaning for substring lengths of the string and pattern.  
* If a state `(i, j)` is solved once, any future reference can reuse the stored result instead of re-computing.  
* This makes the search efficient while keeping the natural recursive structure.  

### Approach
* Keep a 2D table (`memo`) where each entry represents whether `s[0..i-1]` matches `p[0..j-1]`.  
* Apply the same recursive relation but store the result before returning.  
* On each call, first check if `(i, j)` is already computed; reuse if available.  
* Handle all cases of matching (`?`), branching (`*`), and finishing check similarly to recursion but never recompute identical states.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```
/* Function to perform wildcard matching with memoization */
wildCardMatching(i, j, s, p, memo) {
        /* Base case: If both strings are fully processed */
        if (i == 0) {
            if (j == 0) {
                return true /* Both strings match completely */
            }
            if (p[j - 1] == '*') {
                return wildCardMatching(i, j - 1, s, p, memo) /* '*' can match zero characters */
            }
            return false /* Pattern has unmatched characters */
        }

        /* If pattern is fully processed but string is not */
        if (j == 0) {
            return false
        }

        /* Check if the result is already in the memo table */
        if (memo[i][j] is not -1) {
            return memo[i][j]
        }
        /* Case 1: Characters match or pattern has '?' */
        if (s[i - 1] == p[j - 1] or p[j - 1] == '?') {
            memo[i][j] = wildCardMatching(i - 1, j - 1, s, p, memo) /* Process the next characters */
            return memo[i][j]
        }
        /* Case 2: Pattern has '*' */
        if (p[j - 1] == '*') {
            /* Explore both possibilities for '*' */
            matchZero = wildCardMatching(i, j - 1, s, p, memo) /* '*' matches zero characters */
            matchMore = wildCardMatching(i - 1, j, s, p, memo) /* '*' matches one or more characters */
            memo[n][m] = matchZero or matchMore
            return memo[n][m]
        }
        /* Case 3: No match */
        memo[n][m] = false
        return false
}

