# Convert Infix to Postfix

## Solution

### Intuition

* In an infix expression, operands stay in their natural order, but operators must be placed according to precedence and brackets.

* A stack helps us temporarily store operators until we know the correct moment to place them into the postfix answer.

* Whenever we see an operand, we can directly add it to the answer because postfix keeps operands in order.

* The only tricky part is operator handling, especially `^`, because it is right associative, so operators of the same precedence should not always be popped.

### Approach

* Traverse the infix expression from left to right.

* If the current character is an operand, append it directly to the output.

* If it is `(`, push it into the stack. If it is `)`, pop operators into the output until `(` is found.

* If it is an operator, keep popping from the stack while the top operator has higher precedence, or has the same precedence and the current operator is not `^`. Then push the current operator.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={30} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```pseudocode
priority(ch) {
    if (ch == '^') {
        return 3
    }
    if (ch == '*' or ch == '/') {
        return 2
    }
    if (ch == '+' or ch == '-') {
        return 1
    }
    return -1  /* Not an operator */
}

isOperand(ch) {
    /* Check if character is an operand (letter or digit) */
    return (isAlphabet(ch) or isDigit(ch))
}

infixToPostfix(s) {

    stk = empty stack of char
    output = ""  /* Postfix result */

    for each ch in s {
        if (isOperand(ch)) {
            /* Operands go directly to output */
            output = output + ch
        }
        else if (ch == '(') {
            /* Push '(' to mark a new sub-expression */
            stk.push(ch)
        }
        else if (ch == ')') {
            /* Pop until matching '(' is found */
            while (stk is not empty and stk.top() != '(') {
                output = output + stk.top()
                stk.pop()
            }

            /* Remove the '(' from stack */
            stk.pop()
        }
        else {
            /* ch is an operator */
            /* Pop operators from stack to output while they should come before ch */

            while (stk is not empty and stk.top() != '(' and
                   (priority(stk.top()) > priority(ch) or
                   (priority(stk.top()) == priority(ch) and ch != '^'))) {

                /* Pop if stack-top has higher precedence,
                   or same precedence but ch is NOT '^' (because '^' is right-associative) */
                output = output + stk.top()
                stk.pop()
            }

            /* Finally push the current operator */
            stk.push(ch)
        }
    }

    /* Pop any remaining operators */
    while (stk is not empty) {
        output = output + stk.top()
        stk.pop()
    }

    return output  /* Final postfix expression */
}
