# LRU Cache

## Using Doubly Linked List

### Intuition

Think of the cache as a small desk with limited slots to keep your most important papers. The desk is arranged as a **doubly linked list** - each paper knows who is in front of it and who is behind it, so you can remove or move it in constant time without shuffling everything.

The **front** of the list holds the most recently used paper, and the **back** holds the least recently used one.

When you **use a paper** (get operation), you quickly find it through a map, remove it from its current spot in the linked list, and move it to the **front**.

When you **add a new paper** (put operation) and the desk is full, you remove the paper at the **back** (least recently used) and place the new one at the **front**.

The map acts like a quick index telling you exactly where each paper is in the linked list, so every operation happens in **O(1)** time.

### Approach

* Use a doubly linked list to keep track of the order of usage, with most recent at the front and least recent at the back.

* Store key-node references in a map for O(1) access to nodes.

* On `get`, move the accessed node to the front.

* On `put`, update existing keys or add new nodes; if full, remove the least recently used node from the back.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```
/* Doubly linked list node for LRU Cache */
Node {
    /* key-value pair stored in cache */
    key, value    
    /* pointers to previous node and next node */
    prev        
    next        

    /* Constructor to initialize node with key-value */
    Node(_key, _value) {
        key = _key
        value = _value
        prev = next = nullptr
    }
}

solution {
    /* maps key to its node in DLL for O(1) access */
    Map map 
    /* dummy head (most recently used side) and dummy tail (least recently used side) */
    head                    
    tail                    
    /* maximum capacity of cache */
    capacity                  

    /* Initialize cache with given capacity */
    solution(_capacity) {
        capacity = _capacity
        /* dummy head */
        head = new Node(0, 0) 
        /* dummy tail */
        tail = new Node(0, 0)

        /* link head to tail and link tail to head */
        head->next = tail     
        tail->prev = head     
    }

    /* Retrieve value by key and update node as most recently used */
    get(key) {
        if (map.count(key)) {
            /* if key exists in cache, get node, remove it from current position, insert at head (most recent position) */
            node = map[key]       
            remove(node)                
            insert(node)                 
            /* return value */
            return node->value           
        }
        /* key not found */
        return -1                        
    }

    /* Insert or update key-value pair in cache */
    put(key, value) {
        /* if key already exists, remove old node */
        if (map.count(key)) {             
            remove(map[key])             
        }
        if (map.size() == capacity) {     
            /* if cache is full, remove least recently used node */
            remove(tail->prev)          
        }
        /* insert new node at head */
        insert(new Node(key, value))    
    }

    /* Remove node from linked list and map */
    remove(node) {
        /* erase key from map */
        map.erase(node->key)  
        /* bypass node in DLL and maintain DLL links */
        node->prev->next = node->next    
        node->next->prev = node->prev   
    }

    /* Insert node right after head (most recent position) */
    insert(node) {
        /* add key-node mapping */
        map[node->key] = node   
        /* connect new node to head's next and update previous link of old first node */
        node->next = head->next          
        head->next->prev = node 

        /* link head to new node and link new node back to head */
        head->next = node                
        node->prev = head           
    }
}

