# Maximum Items in Container

## Sorting Approach

### Intuition

To maximize the number of items under the 5000-unit limit, we use a greedy strategy that always takes the lightest available item first by sorting all weights and then picking them in ascending order until adding the next one would exceed capacity or we run out of items.

After sorting, we simply walk through the list, keep a running total and count each weight that fits, and stop the moment the cumulative sum would go over 5000.

### Approach

* Sort the items from lightest to heaviest.

* Add each lightest item one by one while the total stays within the weight limit.

* Stop as soon as adding another item would go over the allowed weight.

* The total number of items added is the final result.

### Pseudocode

<CodeBlock language={customtext} showNumberOfLines={15} fontStyle={Normal Code}>

```
maxItemCount(weight) {
    n = weight.size()
    /* Sort the weights in ascending order so we consider lighter items first */
    sort(weight)

    /* Running total of weights selected so far */
    sum = 0
    /* Count of items successfully added */
    ans = 0

    for(i = 0 to n-1){
        /* Add the current weight to the total, If adding this item exceeds capacity, stop immediately */
        sum += weight[i]
        if(sum > 5000){
            break
        }
        /* Otherwise, this item fits, increment our count */
        ans++
    }
    /* Return the total number of items */
    return ans
}
```

